<section class="py-5 mt-5" style="background-color: #fef9e9;">
  <div class="container">
    <!-- Page Title, Problem Description, and Symptoms -->
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-8 col-xl-6 text-center mx-auto">
        <!-- Title in one line -->
        <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold mb-4" style="line-height: 1.2; color: #260d5e;">
          First Aid for Snake Bites When Medical Help is Delayed
        </h1>
        <!-- Brief problem description -->
        <p class="lead text-muted">
          Prompt and proper first aid can reduce venom spread and improve outcomes.
        </p>
        <!-- Short symptoms section in red -->
        <p class="fs-5" style="color: red;">
          <strong>Symptoms:</strong> Swelling, pain, and discoloration at the bite site.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Main Content: Do's and What Not To Do -->
    <div class="row align-items-center">
      <!-- Left Column: Guidelines -->
      <div class="col-md-6">
        <h3 class="fw-bold mb-3">Immediate Steps (Do's):</h3>
        <ol class="fs-5">
          <li>
            <strong>Call Emergency Services:</strong> Dial your local emergency number immediately.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Keep the Victim Calm:</strong> Encourage them to remain as still as possible to slow venom spread.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Immobilize the Affected Limb:</strong> Keep the bitten area at or below heart level.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Remove Constrictive Items:</strong> Remove any jewelry or tight clothing near the bite.
          </li>
        </ol>
        <h3 class="fw-bold mt-4 mb-3">What Not To Do:</h3>
        <ul class="fs-5">
          <li>Do not apply a tourniquet.</li>
          <li>Do not cut or suck the wound.</li>
          <li>Avoid applying ice or cold packs directly to the bite.</li>
          <li>Do not try to excessively flush the wound with water.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-muted mt-3">
          <em>Note:</em> This guide is for emergency use only and does not replace professional medical treatment.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Right Column: Image Placeholder -->
      <div class="col-md-6 text-center">
        <!-- Replace the src attribute with your actual image path -->
        <img src="/assets/img/snakeBite.png" alt="Snake Bite First Aid" class="img-fluid rounded shadow-sm">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

